        <tr class='athing comtr ' id='16525361'><td>
            <table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="40"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_16525361' href='vote?id=16525361&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D16523786'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=cvoss" class="hnuser">cvoss</a> <span class="age"><a href="item?id=16525361">12 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_16525361"></span><span class="par"></span> <a class="togg" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return toggle(event, 16525361)"></a>          <span class='storyon'></span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">A more precise, unit-respecting result is to plot the ratio of the unit sphere&#x27;s volume to the unit cube&#x27;s volume. This is a dimensionless quantity, so it makes sense to compare them, but happily the numeric values are unchanged because the unit cube always has volume 1 m^N in dimension N.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
