        <tr class='athing comtr ' id='16527040'><td>
            <table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="80"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_16527040' href='vote?id=16527040&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D16523786'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=qubex" class="hnuser">qubex</a> <span class="age"><a href="item?id=16527040">5 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_16527040"></span><span class="par"></span> <a class="togg" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return toggle(event, 16527040)"></a>          <span class='storyon'></span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">The more general term for ’area’ and ’volume’ in higher dimensions is ’content’: area is the content of a 2D item, volume is the content of a 3D  item, hypervolume is the content of a 4D item, <i>et cetera</i>.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
                      <u><a href="reply?id=16527040&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D16523786%2316527040">reply</a></u>
                  </font>
